Here we will bound the attacking spots by the queen which is being placed currently. And will do work for only those spots which are not attacked by any queen. I am iterating on rows in recursion so i will make arrays of Column, Diagonal1, Diagonal2. 

Mark the cloumn array and the diagonal array accordingly (which falls under attacking spots).

```
class Solution {

    public static int solve(boolean[] colArr, boolean[] d1, boolean[] d2, int i) {

        if(i == colArr.length) {            
            return 1;
        }
        int sum = 0;
        for(int col = 0; col < colArr.length; col++) {
            if(!colArr[col] && !d1[i + col] && !d2[i - col + colArr.length - 1]) {
                colArr[col] = true;
                d1[i + col] = true;
                d2[i - col + colArr.length - 1] = true;
                sum += solve( colArr, d1, d2, i + 1);
                colArr[col] = false;
                d1[i + col] = false;
                d2[i - col + colArr.length - 1] = false;
            }
        }

        return sum;

    }

    public int totalNQueens(int n) {
        return solve(new boolean[n], new boolean[2*n - 1], new boolean[2*n - 1], 0);
    }
}
