# Approach for this Problem:
1. Initialize three variables currMaxProductSubarr, currMinProductSubarr, maxProductAns to the first element of the input array.
2. Traverse the input array from index 1 to n-1.
3. For each element at index i, update the currMaxProductSubarr and currMinProductSubarr by taking maximum and minimum of the following three values: (i) nums[i], (ii) currMaxProductSubarrnums[i], (iii) currMinProductSubarrnums[i].
4. Update the maxProductAns as the maximum of maxProductAns and currMaxProductSubarr.
5. Return maxProductAns as the final answer.
