# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Here we are taking 3 variables as maxi , mini and res. Which means maxi stores the maximum product till now, mini stores minimum product till now and res stores our answer in it.

So when we iterate over the array we are checking first for maximum product as it was asked in the question, then we are also checking for minimum product because let say we have negative values in our array. lets understand this with an example
mini = -10 right now and maxi = 4
and next element in the array is -2
after this maxi = -10 * -2 = 20
so to get this we are maintaing minimum product also.

Then in res we are storing the maximum value among the 3 variables which we used and return it.

Hope You get this.
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(N)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
