# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
**After reading question carefully, I observed 2 major things**
- The constraints are 10<sup>4</sup> so we can come up with a n<sup>2</sup> solution. That's why I tried a bruteforce solution.
- We have to merge the the intervals again and again which felt like a hassle so I choosed a line sweep method.

# Approach
