## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Here we’ve to sort the 2d array.
- Now, on each iteration check the value of ***small*** because small is the number which is the common middle point for a set of balloons whose\xA0`start point <= small\xA0and\xA0small <= end point.`
- Update the small value when you will find the CurrNode whose start index is greater than the small. Now increment the count and `change small = CurrNode[1]`.
- When the\xA0`CurrNode[0]<small` but the ******`CurrNode[1] < small`\xA0Just simply change the value of `small = CurrNode[1]`, because the given rule of `X start <= small <= X end` will always get obeyed!
- Let’s understand with the following example :

```
[[9,12],[1,10],[4,11],[8,12],[3,9],[6,9],[6,7]]

here the sorted order will be :
1 10
3 9
4 11
6 7
6 9
8 12
9 12

here on the second iteration, 
	small = 10 but the CurrNode = { 3 , 9 } 
	So, CurrNode[1] >= small  BUT  here CurrNode[1] < small, hence to obey the rule:  we will change small from 10 to 9 and 
	1 <= 9 <= 10
	and
	3 <= 9 <= 9
```

- **Time complexity:** O(nlogn).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
class Solution {
public:
    int findMinArrowShots(vector<vector<int>>& points) {

        sort(points.begin(),points.end());

        int small = INT_MIN ;
        int count = 0 ;

        for(auto k:points)
        {
            if( small == INT_MIN )
            {
                small = k[1];
                continue ;
            }
            if( k[0] <= small && small > k[1] )
            {
                small = k[1];
                continue ;
            }
            if( k[0] <= small )
                continue;
            else
            {
                count++ ;
                small = k[1] ;
            }
        }

        return count+1 ;
    }

};
```

