solutions.content:
# Code 1
**Approach** - We are counting how many intervals share a common boundary (overlap).
Now, Number of arrows = Number of Intervals - Number of Overlapping Intervals
```
    int findMinArrowShots(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        sort(begin(points), end(points));
        int overlap = 0, i = 0, n = points.size();
        while(i < n) {
            int x = points[i][0], y = points[i][1];
            while(i+1 < n && points[i+1][0] <= y) {
                overlap++;
                x = max(x, points[i+1][0]);
                y = min(y, points[i+1][1]);
                i++;
            }
            i++;
        }
        return n - overlap;
    }
```

# Code 2 using comparator 
**Approach**- Check how many balloons I can shoot down with one shot aiming at the ending position of the current balloon. 

balloons = [[7,10], [1,5], [3,6], [2,4], [1,4]]
will be sorted as...
balloons = [[2,4], [1,4], [1,5], [3,6], [7,10]]
