# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int findMinArrowShots(int[][] points) {
        Arrays.sort(points, Comparator.comparingInt(o -> o[1])); //Sorting according to end

        int ans = 1;
        int bound = points[0][1];

        for(int i = 1; i<points.length; i++){
            //checking for non-overlapping range
            if(points[i][0] > bound){
                bound = points[i][1];
                ans++;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

# Explanation
- We just need to find the overlapping diameter range. So the easy approach would be to first sort the array.
- Rather than sorting according `start` or `points[][0]` it's better to sort it according to `end` or `points[][1]`.
- This is better because we now only need to check which all balloons have start value less than or equal to the current balloon's end. All these balloons can be popped by the same arrow.
- When we encounter a balloon with start value greater than the current's end we simple make that balloon our current balloon and increment the ans variable.

