# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Sort the element on the basis of start time and calculate the number of distinct points with no overlapping intervals.

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(nlogn)$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(1)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    int findMinArrowShots(vector<vector<int>>& points) {
        sort (points.begin (), points.end ());

        int i = 0;
        int n = points.size (), res = 0;

        while (i < n){
            //in each iteration we start with new point and find
            //corresponding overlapping points in second while loop.
            int start = points[i][0];
            int end = points[i++][1];
            res++;

            while (i < n && start <= points[i][0] && points[i][0] <= end){
                // minimizing width of interval
                start = max (points[i][0],start); 
                end = min (points[i][1], end);
                i++;
            } 

        }

        return res;

    }
};
```

