The intuition here is to find max number of ballons which don't overlap. As this is the biggest such possible set all other ballons can be burst by ony bursting ballons in this set individually.

With this the problem reduces to interval selection problem, i.e. finding largest set of non-overlapping intervals. Python code:
```
class Solution:
    def findMinArrowShots(self, intervals: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        n = len(intervals)
        if n <= 1:
            return n

        intervals.sort(key=lambda x: x[1])
        selected = [intervals[0]]
        for i in range(1,n):
            if intervals[i][0] > selected[-1][1]:
                selected.append(intervals[i])

        return len(selected)
```

